President Obama has nominated Michael A. Hughes to serve as a U.S. Marshal for the Superior Court for the District of Columbia. Hughes has spent his entire law enforcement career with the United States Marshals Service and has held various posts within the organization. He is currently the Chief of the Office of Crisis Services within the Tactical Operations Division. Hughes has also worked with the Witness Security Division and served on the protection detail of the Deputy Attorney General. He previously worked in the office of Senator Frank Lautenberg and holds a bachelor's degree from Montclair State University and a Master of Public Administration degree from American University.